This paper deals with the control of fully-actuated robots, which is a topic within the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the optimization of control frameworks, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of algorithms and simulations to compare different control frameworks could also be relevant to machine learning (cs.MA) and data analysis (cs.LG). Finally, the paper mentions the use of soft and rigid contacts, which could be related to computer vision (cs.CV) in terms of object recognition and tracking.
